    <para id="id11085100">The result can also be seen graphically. The left panel shows both 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>e</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>t</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">/</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{e rSup { size 8{t/4} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> and δ(t+4), and the right panel shows their product.</para>
